  <section class="bg-primary text-white py-4" style="border-radius: 20px;">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="mb-4 text-center">Cardiology</h2>
      <div class="row d-flex align-items-center">
        <div class="col-md-3 text-center">
          <div class="card h-100 border-0 dept-card"  style="box-shadow: 10px 10px 20px 10px #000000f4;">
             <a href="/departments" >
               <img src="/assets/cardiology.jpg" class="card-img-top" alt="Cardiology" style="height: 200px; object-fit: cover; border-radius: 10px 10px 0 0;">
             </a>
           
            <div class="card-body text-center">
              <p class="text-muted small"><bold style="font-size: 15px;color: black;">Heart and vascular treatments with advanced care.</bold></p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-8 px-5">
        <p class="mb-0" style="font-size: 18px;">
Cardiology is the medical specialty devoted to the study, diagnosis, and treatment of heart and blood vessel disorders. Cardiologists focus on conditions such as coronary artery disease, heart failure, arrhythmias, hypertension, and congenital heart defects. This field combines preventive care with advanced interventions, including echocardiography, angioplasty, and pacemaker implantation, to improve patient outcomes. By emphasizing early detection and lifestyle modifications, cardiology helps reduce the risk of life-threatening events like heart attacks and strokes. With rapid advances in technology and treatment methods, cardiology continues to play a vital role in promoting heart health and saving lives worldwide.
        </div>
     </div>
  </section>
