        <div class="col-md-8 px-5">
        <p class="mb-0" style="font-size: 18px;">
Neurology is the branch of medicine dedicated to diagnosing and treating disorders of the brain, spinal cord, and nervous system. Neurologists care for patients with conditions such as stroke, epilepsy, migraines, multiple sclerosis, Parkinson’s disease, and neuropathies. They use advanced diagnostic tools like EEG, MRI, and CT scans to identify complex neurological problems. Treatments may involve medication, lifestyle changes, or advanced therapies tailored to each patient’s needs. Neurology plays a vital role in improving cognitive and motor functions, enhancing quality of life, and providing preventive care for at-risk patients through early detection and effective management of neurological diseases.        </p>
