        <p class="mb-0" style="font-size: 18px;">
Orthopedics is the medical specialty focused on diagnosing, treating, and preventing conditions related to the bones, joints, muscles, ligaments, and tendons. Orthopedic doctors, also known as orthopedists, manage a wide range of problems, including fractures, arthritis, sports injuries, spinal disorders, and congenital deformities. Treatment may involve medication, physiotherapy, minimally invasive procedures, or surgery such as joint replacement. Orthopedics also emphasizes rehabilitation and restoring mobility to improve quality of life. With advancements in surgical techniques and modern technology, orthopedic care helps patients recover faster, regain strength, and return to daily activities with confidence and reduced pain.        </p>
