Dermatology is the branch of medicine that focuses on the skin, hair, and nails. Dermatologists diagnose and treat a wide range of conditions, including acne, eczema, psoriasis, fungal infections, skin cancer, and hair loss. They also perform cosmetic procedures such as laser treatments, chemical peels, and skin rejuvenation. Diagnosis may involve physical examination, biopsy, or laboratory tests. Dermatology emphasizes both medical treatment and aesthetic care, aiming to maintain healthy skin while improving appearance. Preventive measures, early detection, and patient education are key, as healthy skin contributes not only to physical well-being but also to confidence and overall quality of life.        </p>
